«c2»* THE BEST GAMES OF THE PAST! *«»
«»
«c3»BY ZEROX/GODS «c2»with the help of the rest of the D.I.S.C.-Team!«»
«»«as»
«c1»As most sceners first got attracted to the amiga because of the great
games this machine got to offer, it's time to look back and remember the
games we've enjoyed the most.«»
«»
I guess the older sceners will remember great classics as;«»
«»
Spy Vs Spy, Space Invaders, World Games, Marble Madness, Ports Of Call,
Pac Man, Asteroids, Gauntlet, Dig Dug, Donkey Kong, Defender Of The Crown,
Out Run, Ping Pong, Silent Service, Pinguin Adventure, Pooyan, Test Drive
and Qubert among many others.«»
«»
But after the first years of the scene, the games improved even more.
There were no other platforms with such talented graphicians and creators
of games. And a row of great games followed, and I think most of the
present sceners also are familiar with at least some of those games.
Who won't remember games such as Great Giana Sisters, Body Blows,
Lotus Esprit Challenge, Worms, Monkey Island, Colonisation, Leisure Suit Larry,
Conflict, Nuclear War, Lemmings etc. if they've first tried them?«»
«»
At the end of this short article, lets present the games we in the D.I.S.C.
team considers to be the best of all time.«»
«»
